# 1.3b

Insights:-

The above indicates mixed correlation (Includes both positive and negative)

Not even one feature is perfectly correlated with other

P_incidence and S_slope shows more positively correlated and has highest correlation among the given data

P_radius shows neagative correlation with P_incidence, L_angle, S_slope and S_degree, it shows positive correlation only with P_tilt.

P_radius and S_slope are have least correlation.

P_incidence and S_slope have 81% correlation

P_incidence and L_angle have 72% correlation

P_incidence and S_Degree have 64% correlation

P_incidence and P_tilt have 63% correlation.

To conclude P_incidence has better correlation with other features whereas, P_radius has less correlation with other features.

-Along the diagonal we can see distribution of variable for three claases are not same.

-It is evident that type_s class is more compared to other two

-Overall, Scatter plots indicate that type_s is more among all three classes.

-For P_incidence, S_slope and L_angle distribution of (type_s > normal > type_h)

-For P_tilt :- normal > type_s > type_h

-For P_radius :- normal and type_s almost same but at peak normal is slightly greater than type_s and type_h is lower than both the classes.

-For S_Degree :- 'normal' has a sharp high peak followed by type_h and type_s respectively.

-Most of the features doesn't show a clear correlation.

-Overall, P_incidence shows positive correlation with S_slope, L_angle.
